const headHtml = "<title>Passive Bazaar Orders Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based guide to passive bazaar orders in Hypixel SkyBlock, focused on liquid items, slow fills, spread discipline and routines that do not require constant relisting.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/passive-bazaar-orders-guide\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/passive-bazaar-orders-guide\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Passive Bazaar Orders Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Build a low-touch bazaar routine around spreads that survive without all-day babysitting.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Passive Bazaar Orders Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock\",\"description\":\"Expert based guide to passive bazaar orders in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-02-23\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-18\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NotEnoughCoins\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Coflnet GmbH\"},\"url\":\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/passive-bazaar-orders-guide\"}\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-02-23 • Bazaar Flipping</a>\n          <h1>Passive Bazaar Orders Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Not every bazaar player wants to stare at refresh timers all day. Passive bazaar orders exist for the opposite mindset: pick liquid items, post disciplined buy orders, let fills accumulate over time, then unload into markets that can actually absorb size. The current creator material makes this distinction clearer than older flipping advice. Active bazaar flipping is about speed and constant maintenance; passive bazaar orders are about patience, spread quality and avoiding items that only look good in tiny screenshot-sized quantities.</p>\n          <div class=\"note\"><strong>Primary source base:</strong> Xentyl and Kuvdra's bazaar guides, especially the sections on liquidity, buy-order patience and avoiding fake margins.</div>\n          <h2>Passive flipping starts with item selection</h2>\n          <p>The core rule is simple: passive orders only work on items that still move while you are away. If the market is shallow, the order might fill slowly on the way in and then punish you again when you try to exit. That is why creator guides keep returning to volume. A worse-looking spread on a liquid item is often a better passive play than an eye-catching margin on a thin one, because the liquid item can actually cycle capital repeatedly without forcing manual rescue.</p>\n          <p>This is also why low-touch bazaar routines pair well with players who already have another income stream. Farming, slayers or a few manual AH flips can occupy your active playtime while your bazaar orders work in the background. The money is not instant, but it is clean. You are essentially renting out patience to the market and collecting the difference between the two sides of the book.</p>\n          <h2>Patience is part of the method, not a failure state</h2>\n          <p>Players often sabotage passive orders by intervening too quickly. If the spread was chosen correctly and the item is liquid, a slow fill does not mean the order is broken. It often means you are competing in a normal market. The passive approach breaks down when you keep nudging every order upward, turning a patient strategy into a high-maintenance one that gives away edge through constant impatience.</p>\n          <p>Use the live tools to judge whether depth and demand support this style. <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a> ranks items by buy/sell volume, <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a> shows real spread depth, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a> exposes order-book pressure with lowest-BIN context and <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/premiumBazaar\">SkyCofl premium bazaar</a> adds order-flow analytics. <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/manipulate\">Skyblock.bz manipulation feed</a> and <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/crash\">crash risk feed</a> let you sanity-check whether the spread you are seeing belongs to a real market or a momentary distortion. Passive orders are one of the cleanest ways to learn what market quality looks like in practice.</p>\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/bazaar-flipping-guide-2026\">Bazaar Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/npc-to-bazaar-flips\">NPC to Bazaar Flips in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/market-literacy-margin-volume-risk\">How to Read Margin, Volume and Risk Before You Flip</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div><h3>Best paired tools</h3><ul class=\"tool-list\"><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/bazaar\">SkyCofl bazaar</a></li><li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/premiumBazaar\">SkyCofl premium bazaar</a></li><li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/manipulate\">Skyblock.bz manipulation</a></li><li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/bazaar-flipping\">BazaarPro bazaar flipping</a></li></ul></div>\n          <div><h3>Best for</h3><p>Players who want background income without converting SkyBlock into constant relist management.</p></div>\n          <div><h3>Source videos</h3><p>The recent bazaar guides consistently warn that passive orders live or die on liquidity, not headline spread percentages.</p></div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
